      • getTableNamesSortedAccordingToConstraints

        public List<String> getTableNamesSortedAccordingToConstraints(String schemaName)
        Description copied from class: Database
        Return the names of all tables in the given schema sorted according to the foreign key constraints. For example: If TabA has a Parent TabB and TabA is parent of TabC the returned order would be TabB, TabA, TabC Warning: Cycles like TabA refers to TabB which refers to TabA are not guaranteed to be handled correctly or to be detected
        Overrides:
        getTableNamesSortedAccordingToConstraints in class Database
        Parameters:
        schemaName - The schema, not null
        Returns:
        The names of all tables in the database - sorted
